\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 56. S. otites} (L.) Wibel,{\i  Prim. Fl. Werthem.} 241 (1799). Stems 10-50(-140) cm. Basal leaves narrowly spathulate; cauline leaves few and small with little or no development of axillary leafy shoots. Calyx 3-4 mm, ovoid, glabrous; teeth obtuse. Petal-limb inconspicuous, greenish, linear. Capsule (3·5-)4-5(-5·5) mm, ovoid to subglobose, exceeding the calyx; carpophore usually c. 1 mm.{\i  S.C. & W. Europe, from C. Spain eastwards to Lithuania and Bulgaria.} Al Au Br Bu Cz Da Ga Ge Gr He Ho Hs Hu It Ju Po ?Rm Rs(B) Tu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 A very variable species. At least two subspecies can be recognized.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b otites} : Stems usually less than 50 cm. Seeds smooth. 2n = 24. {\i  Almost throughout the range of the species}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b hungarica }Wrigley, {\i Ann. Bot. Fenn.}{\b  23:} 74 (1986): Stems usually at least 50 cm. Seeds tuberculate. •{\i  E.C. Europe}.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 These subspecies are linked by intermediate populations; subsp. ({\b b}) may have arisen through introgressive hybridization with {\b 57},{\b  61} and perhaps {\b 60}.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 {\b S}. ×{\b  pseudotites} Besser ex Reichenb.,{\i  Fl. Germ. Excurs.} 819 (1832), a tall plant with broadly spathulate basal leaves with undulate margins, spreading panicles and larger, subglobose capsules, occurs in N. Italy and S.E. France. This plant has sometimes been included in {\b 56}, but has been shown to be a hybrid between {\b 56} and{\b  58} (vide F. Wrigley, {\i Ann. Bot. Fenn.}{\b  23:} 69-81 (1986)).
\par

