\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 57. S. donetzica} Kleopow, {\i Jour. Inst. Bot. Acad. Sci. Ukr.}{\b  9:} 116 (1936) ({\i S. sillingeri} Hendrych). Like {\b 56} but stems robust, 90-150(-170) cm, with dense, short pubescence (up to 0·1 mm); internodes 4-8, very viscid; basal leaves oblanceolate-spathulate; cauline leaves numerous, with leafy shoots developed in the axils; inflorescence very dense with condensed verticillasters; ultimate dichasia with very short peduncles; flowers often subsessile; seeds larger, tuberculate. •{\i  C. & E. Europe from E. Czechoslovakia to E. Ukraine}. Cz Hu Rm Rs(C, W, E).
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 58. S. colpophylla} Wrigley, {\i Ann. Bot. Fenn.}{\b  23:} 77 (1986). Stems usually 100-150 cm, pubescent below, glabrous above. Basal leaves broadly spathulate, with undulate margins, densely pubescent; cauline leaves few, with little development of axillary leafy shoots. Inflorescence somewhat lax, with distinctly stalked dichasia. Calyx 3·5-4·5 mm, cylindrical-campanulate, glabrous. Petals yellowish. Capsule 6-6·5 mm, ovoid; carpophore c. 0·7 mm. Seeds large, smooth, with tuberculate margin. •{\i  S.E. France} ({\i Provence}). Ga.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 59. S. densiflora} D'Urv.,{\i  Mém. Soc. Linn. Paris}{\b  1:} 303 (1822) ({\i Otites dolichocarpa} Klokov). Like {\b 58} but smaller (up to 110 cm), the stem pilose below, with 2-7 very viscid internodes; inflorescence with more or less condensed verticillasters; ultimate dichasia with very short peduncles, and flowers often subsessile.{\i  S. Ukraine}. Rs(W, K, E)
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 60. S. exaltata} Friv.,{\i  Flora }({\i Regensb}.){\b  18:} 333 (1835) ({\i Otites exaltata} (Friv.) J. Holub). Stems up to 200 cm, with hairs more than 1·5 mm in the lower part. Cauline leaves many, oblanceolate, becoming revolute, with leafy shoots developed in the axils. Inflorescence lax, acuminate, with subsessile dichasia. Flowers somewhat fragrant; petals pale yellow. Calyx 3-3·5 mm. Capsule c. 5·5 mm; carpophore c. 1 mm. Seeds c. 1·3 mm, more or less smooth. •{\i  S.E. Europe.} Bu Gr Ju Rm.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 61. S. chersonensis} (Zapal.) Kleopow, {\i Bull. Jard. Bot. Kiev}{\b  9:} 9 (1929) (incl.{\i  Otites moldavica} Klokov). Like {\b 60} but shorter (up to 150 cm); cauline leaves patent or somewhat deflexed; inflorescence not acuminate, the dichasia stalked; flowers fragrant; petals dark yellow; capsule c. 4·8 mm; seeds c. 0·8 mm, tuberculate. •{\i  S.E. Europe.} Rm Rs(C, W, K, E).
\par

