\pard\f0\fs28 Sect. ODONTOPETALAE Schischkin ex Chowdhuri. Perennials with woody stock; flowering stems lateral in axils of basal leaves. Flowers large, solitary or in few-flowered dichasia. Calyx more or less inflated, hairy, 10-veined. Petals with bifid limb toothed near base, and auriculate claw; coronal scales present. Capsule unilocular, without basal septa.
\par

