\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 62. S. auriculata} Sm. in Sibth. & Sm.,{\i  Fl. Graec. Prodr.}{\b  1: }301 (1809) (incl. {\i S. lanuginosa} Bertol.). Caespitose, with short, branched, woody stock and robust, 1- to few-flowered, pubescent stems up to 30 cm. Basal leaves up to 12 cm, lanceolate, acute, thick, with roughly punctate surface, densely ciliate with undulate hairs 1-2 mm; cauline leaves 1-3 pairs, small, remote. Calyx 12-15 mm, densely glandular-hairy; teeth triangular, acute. Petals white or cream; limb 5-8 mm; claw exserted. Capsule c. 3 times as long as carpophore, ovoid, enclosed within calyx. 2n = 24. {\i Crevices of limestone rocks. • Mountains of Italy} ({\i Alpi Apuane}) {\i and Greece}. Gr It.
\par

